      { type: "p", text: "Walk out of your office right now and stand on your factory floor. Look at the specific parts coming off the line. Ask yourself: Who are these parts actually for? Are these machines actively building a highly profitable, defensible reputation, or are we just renting out our spindle hours to the lowest bidder?" },
      { type: "p", text: "Most manufacturing founders spend their entire lives trapped in the operational weeds, blind to the structural reality of their own business. They work incredibly hard, yet they remain entirely invisible to the market." },
      { type: "figure", title: "The Strategic Moat", visual: "A highly complex, specialized industrial part (like a medical wiring harness or an aerospace bracket) resting safely inside a heavy, impenetrable medieval fortress wall.", caption: "True strategy doesn't just win you a premium order; it builds an uncopyable fortress around your margins." },
      { type: "p", text: "They believe strategy is a luxury reserved for massive multinational corporations. In reality, strategy begins with something much simpler, and much harder. Strategy begins with better questions." },
      { type: "p", text: "It begins with the courage to stop accepting every drawing that comes across your desk. It begins with the profound, terrifying realisation that you cannot be everything to everyone." },
      { type: "quote", text: "When you decide not to quote for a job because it falls outside your new 'Where to Play' criteria, that is strategy. When you refuse to drop your price to match a cheap competitor because you know your 'How to Win' delivers uncopyable value, that is strategy." },
      { type: "h2", text: "The Next Challenge" },
      { type: "p", text: "If you have completed the worksheets in this book, you have already taken the hardest step. You have diagnosed the exact structural flaws in your business model." },
      { type: "p", text: "The era of accumulating random orders is over. It is time to make choices. It is time to start winning." }
    ]
  }
